---
// Mirror's Edge Moon — nrbts.world portfolio
// Stage 1: Astro scaffold + Three.js canvas rendering a plain sphere.
// Stage 9: manual sun/moon override control (Live / Day / Night), so the
// scene can be demoed without waiting on the real clock.
//
// Stage 10: real content layer. The scene becomes a fixed full-viewport
// backdrop (canvas position: fixed) and the actual page content — about,
// projects, skills/resume, contact — scrolls over it in normal document
// flow, so the city/sky stays visible and time-of-day-reactive throughout
// the whole page, not just a single hero screen.
//
// Design pass (post-scaffold feedback): moved away from dark glassy rounded
// "startup" cards toward an off-white/grey, angular, Mirror's-Edge-coded
// look — solid light panels with a cut top-right corner instead of
// border-radius, a bold geometric display face (Chakra Petch) for
// headlines paired with the existing system sans for body copy and mono
// for metadata/tags. Hero no longer states a name (that lives in About now)
// — instead it states capabilities.
//
// Content: About/Projects/Skills/Contact are all real (Norbert, Portland OR,
// creative production across Nike/adidas). Resume link points at the real
// PDF in public/resume/ — replace that file if the CV is ever updated.
